maintext:
Phoenix police ID man who was fatally shot over weekend
PHOENIX (AP) — Police have identified a man who was fatally shot in Phoenix over the weekend.
Police said Monday that 25-year-old Drew James was found with a gunshot wound around 11:30 p.m. Saturday at an apartment complex. He was taken to a local hospital where he was pronounced dead.
Police say they haven’t found any suspect or possible motive for the shooting yet.
Detectives are continuing to investigate the case.
